         <div xml:lang="en" type="translation">
            <ab>Side 2: The ninth year, Pachon 27, through Dioscorus and Touteos (?) and partners, collectors of money-taxes at the village of Euhemeria. You have paid and I have received on account of the payment for the oil-taxes of the eighth year...fifty-six drachmae, total 56 dr., which sum we will pay to the treasury in the name of you, Apollonius, and will hand over to you the treasury receipt. (Grenfell, Hunt &amp; Hogarth)</ab>
         </div>
